Back in Texas but mom’s still thinking about these words from our trip back to NY. And all the change that she once made happen in that dark room in NoHo Soulcycle. She wonders if she had that same space in 2018, when she went through the darkest period of her life, if she would have come out of it quicker. If she would have moved through it better. But whatever happened, she knows that when that thing didn’t work out… she was saved. She grew stronger, better, more empathetic, more resilient. We grew closer, we had bigger adventures, we traveled more, we did things that brought us both joy. More of that please.

Hellos! I have been away from social media all summer and have some exciting news to share! 
Mom and I have been traveling around this summer and visiting family. We decided to move to a new house a mile up the road from where we used to live, and are settling into our new home. Mom got me a backyard and a lot more space that is much more us. Mom also decided to leave her job after a lot of thoughtful consideration so her last day is the end of this month. 🥳🥳🥳 for me! I get her to fetch full time. 

So what did we learn on our social media sabbatical? Well. We don’t miss it. Except for sharing businesses and creatives like @redwolfgroomer and her talents like my beautiful floof and feathers. Which is important to us. Very important. 

Mom said it helped her listen to her own voice. It helped her focus on her life and decisions that needed to be made. 

As we go into a new season and her new chapter, we will maintain that absence a little longer through the transition. Mom is taking a long break from work to shift her attention, travel, take me on some adventures, be creative and focus on ❤️. 

She’s also going to be doing creative consulting work for doggo friendly local businesses so watch out for more deets!

We missed you too… and so we will be back. 

xoxo 
Poppy + Sam

#hello #dogmomlife #dogmom #dogsofinstagram

Hellos. Good Mornings. I just wanted to wish you all a good week full of lots of treatos and pup cups. And coffee for your humans. I had a magical weekend when my mom’s friend came to visit me. @coronalikethebeer13 and I snuggled last night before she went back home to her cat, Bubbles, and a more humane climate. ok that is all i have for story time. byeee.

THE DAY HAS FINALLY ARRIVED! 

Mom’s attention is all mine. I worked really hard over the last (almost) 8 years to get to her to stop working and spend all her time with me and it finally paid off. 

She’s taking me on a vacation to the beach to celebrate my birthday this month. My grandmaw is flying to Texas to visit me. And she signed me up for some fun classes. Let’s not forget all the walkies and fetch we’re going to do. Tacos, tacos will happen too. 

Truth is, my mom misses posting our adventures. So while she has no intention of rejoining her own account… we are going to share on here. 

Here I am, listening to her tell me about our week ahead!

Before I head off to enjoy the day…. PLEASE do not send my mom memes or reels. the truth is, she’s going to be spending a lot of time focusing on what she wants to do next in life and away from her phone. her intention for joining instagram 7 years ago was to find a community of dog owners who were also looking for dog friendly businesses and adventures. over time it also grew to support local businesses and brands. small brands. local brands. go ahead and share these! NOT memes or jokes or meme accounts or time wasting posts. 
.
.
.
.
.
.

I know a lot of dog owners will say this and all of them are right when they do- becoming one will change your life. Happy Birthday, Poppy Mae. 8 years ago, she and 8 other puppies came into this world at @creampufflabradoodles and 8 weeks later I took this floof home. I was half terrified and half excited beyond words. 

I always said I’d never get a dog until I could give it the life it deserved. And while not every day is a romp around the shoreline at golden hour, 98% of the time my world revolves around Poppy and I’m totally ok with that because 

I have learned more about myself and become a better person because of her. She is my once in a life time dog, best friend and companion. And she is a member of the family. 

For Poppy’s birthday, I took her to our happy place. She inspires and motivates me to travel when I need to get out of my routine most and to sit on a beach or walk along the ocean and work through the hardest questions in life. 

Whatever I think she needs, is always what I do. A walk, a nap, a vacation… I have always had a hard time putting myself first and she helps me do that in so many ways. I was needing the ocean, the sand, the stillness, sunsets and sunrises, and no where to be but outside. Her birthday just seemed like a good excuse to leave the 100 degree heat in landlocked Texas and smell the salty air that reminds me of where I grew up. 

Thank you to @dolittles and @crewlala for the southern hospitality, our dear friends for having us for dinner and Poppy’s bark day macaron, and a fun evening at the brewery tonight. 

We will see you sooner than we know it, Kiawah. ❤️ #kiawahisland

I posted a poem for you by @zachlanebryan so turn up the sound and read below 👇🏼

I am loyal to a fault to anyone I find kindness in
I do not and will not fear tomorrow because I feel as though today has been enough
And I got no hate in my heart for anything, anywhere, or anyone
And I think fear and Fridays got an awful lot in common, they are overdone and glorified and always leave you wanting

next, thank you for the bark day wishes. 

We haven’t been so good at keeping up with instagram the last year while choosing to prioritize other things that felt more important to us but it is very nice to see so many of our friends here wishing me a happy birthday and .. and… READING the post. 

Apparently humans still read posts! 

About fear and fridays… my mom is embarking on a new chapter of her life and she strongly encourages you to look fear in the face and do something you always know you could but were always afraid to try. You don’t need to quit your job but maybe try a marathon, ask that person you like out, get a puppy, go on a solo trip, try playing tennis, take a dance class, start that sewing project, learn to paint. Whatever you want to do, look past your excuses of not having enough time and stop reading my post and wasting it. You scroll a lot more than you think you do… and you could be doing something that makes you… well, YOU. 

#birthdaygirl #dogbirthday #dogfashion #dogmom #onlydog #onlychild #dogsofaustin #crewlala #zacbrownband #rhymes #music #doglife #inspiration

Not a glamorous post but… an authentic one. I am thankful for @faith_weeks and the entire @firehouseanimal team on this Thanksgiving eve. I had another pretty bad ear infection. And mom was concerned about the doggo virus going around. Dr. Weeks took care of me and we came up with a list of places to avoid while also ensuring my flu vaccine was current. And guess what? I got a pup cup while they injected me! We love firehouse. I’m also thankful for @trupanion - as always. 

It’s so important to have a good pet insurance and they’re the best. We checked out and in under one minute, we found out what was covered and how much we owed (ear infections covered, vaccine is preventative so it is not and that’s ok). 

Knowing we don’t have to worry about huge medical bills whenever we go visit Dr Weeks is a big relief. Especially with doggo viruses going around. 

For the cost of 1-2 bandanas a month, you can have peace of mind. 

We have a fun day ahead tomorrow with our friends like family. Happy Thanksgiving everyone. We are thankful for so many things this year… especially you. 

#thankful #vet #trupanion #petinsurance #vetvisit #dogsofinstagram #doghealth #thanksgiving

I promise you, we won’t always do reels. We love the original format of IG the most. There is a lot more feeling in a still photo, at least we think so. 

We read something like 80% of creators have burnout. Sounds about right… creating, editing, and producing ORIGINAL content can be exhausting for most people. Many accounts have social media teams… trying to keep up with them, family, full time job and sleep is too much most days. 

Mom doesn’t believe you need to do these things. Some of her favorite accounts are not reels and continue to grow because they share useful content, are authentic and original, and are relatable because they’re imperfect. 

Now back to the photo… Here I am, locked on a great dane with his dad… they were having the best time together at @butlerpitchandputt on a Sunday evening. No phone in sight. That’s what it’s all about 99% of the time. Staying present and enjoying your pup. you can take our photo 1%… but only if there’s treats! 

The weather has started to turn colder and we are enjoying those crisp days here in Austin. I love to keep warm in this reversible vest…

I am really lucky to have some awesome kids in the neighborhood who come knock on our door to play with me. 

And today a few of them stopped by on their day off and wanted to hang out. Thankfully, these girls aren’t big into screen time and when my mom said they could go play in my closet and dress me up, they got SUPER EXCITED. 

She handed them a bunch of sweet potato treatos and off we went to play dress up. 

HOW FUN are these outfits? 

It’s so heart warming to see creativity flowing from kids. @glennondoyle says we rob kids of boredom when we give them screens. 

Mom posted some of the videos to my stories today and she had more ❤️s and comments than any other story she’s ever posted. Because it’s fun. And joyful. And real. 

We wanted to share this video with you…
